description: Central Park is the 843-acre green heart of Manhattan and is maintained by the Central Park Conservancy. It was designed in the 19th century by Frederick Law Olmsted and Calvert Vaux as an urban escape for New Yorkers, and now receives over 40 million visits per year.

description: The Port Authority Bus Terminal (PABT) is the main gateway for interstate buses into Manhattan in New York City. The terminal is the largest in the United States and the busiest in the world by volume of traffic, serving about 7,000 buses and 200,000 people on an average weekday.

tips: [[4c338c2a6f1fef3bb994ec3d, Today Queen Elizabeth plans to visit the site for the first time and will lay a wreath in tribute to the thousands who died in the 9/11 attack, including 67 Britons.], [4ecc799a9adf1839a132bee3, President Obama and the First Lady along with former President George W. Bush and former First Lady Laura Bush, paused at the North Memorial Pool on the tenth anniversary of the 9/11 attacks.], [4baf313370c603bbb4f595b4, If you're in NYC, go pay your respects. Its the least any of us can do.], [517acbdbe4b0dbb220311b59, How anyone can pose for pictures here much less smile in them is unfathomable.], [504f7e06e4b098d93b57a08f, Today is a day of remembrance . God bless United States. God bless world. ], [522054c511d2065bc876a9f7, プールに刻まれた文字は、9.11で犠牲になった約3000名のお名前です。名前の配列には犠牲者が当時いた場所や遺族の希望が反映されているそうです。], [50a41954e4b04e2d5c99a4a5, It is important to remember!], [5095546f498e4ddf6827d27f, Carry a flower or a wreath to pay tribute to the 9_11 victims.so sad], [51d088e5498e99bf5a1db53c, Seeing it in person almost brought me to my knees. I cannot imagine a better tribute to the fallen. Watch the water ripple in the falls. It makes almost human images, like shadows. Breathtaking.], [4e808f30b8f7d6b24bcdf2a0, In the footsteps of the original Twin Towers lie two reflecting pools where visitors can pay their respects and see the bronze inscribed names of those who lost their lives.], [504f9093e4b09745bfc0e537, One day that changed not only the landscape of New York,  but changed the entire world.], [5220d7b111d2e279e78aef77, Take a moment of silence to remember the courage that day. This is sacred ground where thousands died, not a place for you to take a smiley family photo and let your bratty kids run amok.], [4e6b36771fc7f7282e5463d0, The Memorial consists of two waterfalls created in the former foundations of the twin towers. Lines can be very long!], [52028d4b498ee8042c1557d8, Make sure you visit the survivor tree!], [51cca7fe498e798f63b4a068, Never Forget.], [50593476e4b0fd1a4918dc24, Sobering moments, well worth paying tribute... We will never forget!]]

description: The National September 11 Memorial is a tribute of remembrance and honor to the nearly 3,000 people killed in the terror attacks of September 11, 2001 at the World Trade Center site, near Shanksville, Pa., and at the Pentagon, as well as the six people killed in the WTC bombing in February 1993.

tips: [[51ccefc5498eb167afd96334, Hidden behind the wall at the first bay near the rotunda is a ceramic tile mural done by Joan Miró. The work was commissioned by museum trustee Harry F. Guggenheim in 1963 to honor his late wife.], [4e0c6b046365bebd0bc6fb4b, Frank Lloyd Wright originally intended for Guggenheim visitors to take the elevator up and stroll down the ramps. Today, exhibitions are viewed both ways. The choice is yours!], [5203c041498e880757c6ba27,  Imagine this summer’s show at the Guggenheim Museum as air-conditioning for the eye and, if you’re gamely susceptible, the soul. ], [4c8a9605106d76b00790f00b, Catch fall shows  Chaos and Classicism: Art in France, Italy, and Germany  (Oct 1) and  Vox Populi: Posters of the Interwar Years  (Sept 1) between 5:45pm-7:45pm on Saturdays when admission is free.], [4acb8ada70c603bb8c8e8eb4, Most people walk the main spiral, but the smaller staircases usually house exhibits by more emerging artists.], [4bed74af70c603bb03789bb4, Check out Julie Mehretu's exhibition,  Grey Area,  her representation of post-war Berlin in which the dynamism of urban life confronts decay and change. It's open through October 6, 2010.], [50edd17ee4b0e7254226a20f, Picasso Black and White is an on-going exhibition at the Guggenheim Museum to showcase Pablo Picasso's artworks in black and white throughout his prolific career from 1904-1971. Continues January 23.], [4de6aa5a8130690dbf112cb3, During its seasonal Art After Dark events, Frank Lloyd Wright’s iconic building is electrified with after-hours chic. Have a cocktail while listening to an artist- or curator-selected playlist.], [5443d7f1498e7cfb8d3689e6, Frank Lloyd Wright’s architectural dream rivals the concept-driven modern art exhibits inside the museum. Audio guide is a good option & get a look at the boosktore  ], [4e8b304130f82dd42bed6328, A fantastic art museum with many famous works situated on a unique spiral walkway.  When you walk into the main area, look up!  It makes for a great photo.], [50eef2ece4b033522b6c564e, Ask the Gallery Guides (with the big  Ask Me!  buttons) about the art! Even if you don't have a specific question, ask something like,  What is going on here?  They are super smart & friendly! Do it.], [4c8a982975ba9c74c0ee525c, Frank Lloyd Wright's postwar jewel was protested by many artists when he debuted, but it has become a modern landmark for the city.], [4e1b687ccc3f9d5b594fe48c, Check out  Kandinsky at the Bauhaus, 1922–1933  from the permanent collection.], [4f11b4d5e4b07e9ecaae5744, World famous for a reason! Gotta go up the spiral walkway. Don't try and skateboard down it though...], [4cb8f65c352ebfb73d6c8cf2, In the opening scene of 1997's  Men in Black  Will Smith's pursuit of a criminal through the streets of NYC concludes at the Guggenheim. Its here that he realizes this criminal might not be human...], [4fd402f4e4b088343ae5aaec, Take the elevator to the top and work your way down. Walking down the spiral is much easier. Added bonus: you get to see all the art walking downstairs when leaving if it's closing time.], [51859b33498e4d97acf9dcb5, don't wear heels to this museum. the whole thing is one big hill.], [4e77bf8e8998834aa3a8ec6c, The building itself is a work to be pondered, but the exhibits are always stimulating and hold true to the museum’s form and intent.], [4ee6741f722e088261925e55, The building itself is the main draw here, but don’t miss the exhibits, which are intellectually challenging and interesting.  Closed on Thursdays!], [4e8b8829c2eeff1f321ef416, Home to modern masterpieces, the building itself is a a huge draw too.
